The patient is a 48-year-old male on chronic prednisone with a prosthetic mitral valve who developed endocarditis due to Corynebacterium propinquum. The narrative describes a pre-existing condition (prosthetic valve endocarditis) caused by a specific pathogen. The patient was treated with ceftriaxone, not daptomycin; the narrative explicitly states the pathogen was resistant to daptomycin. Therefore, the event (endocarditis) is not an adverse reaction to daptomycin but a primary infection that the drug was not used to treat. There is no temporal link to daptomycin administration. The score is 0 as the event occurred independent of the drug.

