The patient narrative describes three cases of thrombocytopenia occurring during COVID-19 infection. The patients were subsequently treated with eltrombopag, which is a thrombopoietin receptor agonist used to treat thrombocytopenia. The narrative indicates that the thrombocytopenia was 'associated with' the COVID-19 infection and the treatment was initiated in response to this condition. Since the drug was administered to treat the pre-existing condition, it is not the cause of the adverse event. Therefore, the causal relationship to eltrombopag is Doubtful. The event is serious as it was 'life-threatening' and required hospitalization. The MedDRA PT is 'Thrombocytopenia'. The event is 'Unexpected' for eltrombopag as an adverse drug reaction, as the drug is intended to increase platelet counts, not cause thrombocytopenia.

